Sentencas: In this study, Ce0.8Sr0.2Fe0.9Ir0.1O3-delta (CSFI) nanophase material was prepared by sol-gel technique, characterised, and then tested as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells operating between 300-500 degrees C.
Titulo: Evaluation of Novel Nanophase Ce0.8Sr0.2Fe0.9Ir0.1O3-δ as Cathode Material for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: The materials were studied using X-ray diffraction, Raman spectroscopy, Fourier transform infrared spectroscopy, and thermogravimetric analysis.
Titulo: Evaluation of Novel Nanophase Ce0.8Sr0.2Fe0.9Ir0.1O3-δ as Cathode Material for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: The morphology was examined using scanning electron microscopy and high resolution transmission electron microscopy.
Titulo: Evaluation of Novel Nanophase Ce0.8Sr0.2Fe0.9Ir0.1O3-δ as Cathode Material for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Samples showed changes in the overall structure and defect chemistry with an increase in calcination temperature.
Titulo: Evaluation of Novel Nanophase Ce0.8Sr0.2Fe0.9Ir0.1O3-δ as Cathode Material for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: When tested as cathode materials, the material calcined at 1000 degrees C had the greatest performance at a test temperature of 500 degrees C, with a current density of 774.47 mA/cm(2), a power density of 483.07 mW/cm(2) and an area specific resistance (ASR) of 0.342 Omega/cm(2).
Titulo: Evaluation of Novel Nanophase Ce0.8Sr0.2Fe0.9Ir0.1O3-δ as Cathode Material for Low Temperature SOFC
